1326+ 7209              // (number)     d a -- d1 a1
1327+ 7209              // using the current BASE parse characters stored in address a
1328+ 7209              // accumulating a double precision integer d
1329+ 7209              // the process stops at the first not-convertible character
1330+ 7209              // A double-number is kept in CPU registers as HLDE.
1331+ 7209              // On the stack a double number is treated as two single numbers
1332+ 7209              // where HL is on the top of the stack and DE is the second from top,
1333+ 7209              // so in the stack memory it appears as LHED.
